SMS Terms of Use – ACTIVA ENVIRONNEMENT

By subscribing (“Opt-In”) or using the ACTIVA ENVIRONNEMENT text messaging service (as defined below), you agree to these Terms & Conditions.

This agreement is between you and ACTIVA ENVIRONNEMENT, located at: 106, rue Industrielle, New Richmond (Québec), G0C 2B0.

Definitions

“Opt-In”: means requesting, accepting, enrolling, confirming, or consenting to receive one or more text messages.

“Text Messaging Service”: includes any instance in which we send one or more messages to your mobile phone number, including SMS, MMS, or equivalent technologies.

Consent to Text Messaging
By agreeing to receive text messages from us, you accept these Terms of Use, as well as our general Terms and Privacy Policy, which are incorporated by reference.

Electronic Consent
By agreeing to receive text messages, you also consent to the use of an electronic record to document your agreement. You may withdraw your consent by replying STOP.

SMS Privacy Policy
We respect your privacy. Information you provide via this service is used solely to send messages to you and respond to your requests. This may include sharing with platform providers, mobile carriers, and technical service providers.
Your information will never be shared for marketing purposes. However, we reserve the right to disclose information if required by law or to protect our rights.

Message Costs
We do not charge for sending or receiving messages through this service. Standard message and data rates may apply according to your mobile carrier.

Opt-Out
To stop receiving messages, reply to any SMS with STOP, QUIT, END, CANCEL, or UNSUBSCRIBE. After unsubscribing, a confirmation message may be sent.

Additional Legal Notices
For assistance, reply HELP to the number you contacted. Review our full Privacy Policy at [Privacy Policy Link]. Terms and Conditions are available on our website.

Contact & Support
For any assistance, contact us at support@activaenviro.ca
.

